Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @Red Onion{1}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @Red Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, @Sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Cover tightly with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until sugar has dissolved, ~{1%minute}.

Keep covered, stirring occasionally, until ready to use in Step 5.

Remove @Italian Pork Sausage Mix{9%oz} from casing if necessary; discard casing. Form into two patties, each slightly wider than a burger bun.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

In the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, top patties with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup}; cover pan to melt cheese.

While patties cook, in a second small #bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and as much @Hot Sauce{1%tsp} as you like. Set aside until ready to serve.

Lightly crush @Croutons{1} in bag.

Drain liquid from pickled onion into a large bowl; return drained onion to small bowl and set aside.

To bowl with pickling liquid, add @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}; whisk to combine. Add @Arugula{2%oz} and crushed croutons; toss to combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Halve and toast @Potato Bun{2}.

Evenly spread cut sides of buns with spicy mayo. Fill buns with patties and as much pickled onion as you like.

Divide burgers and salad between plates.

> Add any remaining pickled onion to salad if desired.

> Pork Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.